name: Delta Air Lines McDonnell-Douglas MD-90 GORGEOUS Sunset Arrival in Atlanta!
description:
The MD-90 is a stretched version of the venerable MD-80 series with updated engines, and this was my first flight on one! This two hour hop down to Atlanta Hartsfield Jackson was on board N952DN, a 1998-built MD-90 that initially flew with Japan Airlines before being acquired by Delta in 2012. It was great to finally add an MD-90 to my flight log, and this arrival came with some incredible lighting! Hope you enjoy this approach and landing into the world's busiest airport.

Thanks for watching!
